-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-29/more-libya-plans-cabinet-shuffle-after-violence-in-benghazi.html
Prime Minister Ali Zaidan said today
in news conference he’ll present his nominations to parliament
in coming days, including a new defense chief.
* He said there are plans to resurrect two agencies -- one
tasked with internal security and another with forensics -- to
ensure govt gets intelligence on planning of crimes.
* Only the General Intelligence agency is currently operating,
it deals with  Libya ’s external security while all other state
institutions are “ruined": Zaidan
NOTE: At least 43 people wounded in attack near courthouse and
prosecutor’s office in Benghazi yday. Three people - a Libyan
human rights activist, a police colonel and retired airforce
colonel - were killed in separate attacks in the city July 26, a
day later more than 1,000 inmates escaped from jail  To contact the reporter on this story:
